snippet.textDisplay:
I'm a grown 39 year old man and I cried as if it was my own family who passed. My heart aches for this family. I myself have two little girls, and can not help but think what was going through those parents mind. I keep thinking that they must have had a least 30 seconds to realized something bad was going to happen and is completely helpless, helpless to protect your children.

I can't help myself to think how the universe, how god had this planned out for Kobe. The fact that the interview with Lebron on the day he surpassed Kobe's record. Did anyone else thought the way Lebron spoke about Kobe as if it was a remembrance? (Kobe was still well and alive at that time) The fact that He retired, spent the last years spending as much time with his family pushing them out to the fore front of the world since they've been in the background. Just as he finally started to come out more to let us, the world see his next big step in life, showing up to alot of games. Giving him time to do all these great things before he was taken from us, from his family. Life is crazy. I think of Kobe literally as a superhero where he's immortal, untouchable, will live on, nothing can ever happen to him, so hearing that he died shook me to my core. My hands were shaking trying to google if it was true, but my gut told me, dude, its reported by TMZ so it had to be true. I am so devastated as everyone else. He's a wonderful person that God created to set a life example to be a good person and that it does not matter who you are, you can be taken at anytime.

I pray for his family and the rest of the other families. This lost is a big one.
